data.name: Label6.Text
data.value: We are a community of over 500 people: 400 undergraduate students, 25 resident tutors and scholars drawn from Harvard’s graduate and professional schools, and over 75 affiliated faculty and visiting scholars.

data.name: Label5.Text
data.value: Students at Radcliffe College first took up residence on campus in 1901; apparently, the oldest parts of PfoHo date to that year. During the 1949-50 academic year, Moors opened and was first drawn up.

data.name: Label3.Text
data.value: Mather is composed of two modern buildings: the Low-rise surrounds a courtyard, from which one gains entry to the Dining Hall, House offices, classrooms, the Junior Common Room, Senior Common Room.
